ZCZC OE46
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 162300 UTC
A LARGE LOW COMPLEX WILL REMAIN SLOW-MOV OVER SCANDINAVIA
THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD. ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A VIGOROUS
LOW IS EXP TO BE CENTRED NEAR NW SCOTLAND AROUND 984
WITH FURTHER SMALL SCALE LOWS OR TROUGHS TO THE W OF
PORTPATRICK. THIS COMPLEX SERIES OF LOW PRESSURES WILL
GRADUALLY TRANSFER EWARDS ACROSS THE N SEA AND INTO
SCANDINAVIA AND NERN GERMANY BY SATURDAY. HIGH PRESSURE
CENTRED OVER IBERIA AT FIRST 1031 WILL DECLINE AS A
HIGH DEVELOPS IN MID ATLANTIC BY SATURDAY AROUND 1040. A
STRG NW AIRSTREAM WILL THEN BECOME ESTABLISHED ACROSS THE
WHOLE UK AND SURROUNDING SEA AREAS. STRG TO GALE FORCE
WINDS ARE EXP TO PERSIST ACROSS THE WHOLE OF PORTPATRICK
THROUGH THIS PERIOD WITH SEV GALES LIKELY AT TIMES
THESE PERHAPS MORE LIKELY ON THURSDAY AND AGAIN ON
SATURDAY. ANY MODERATION IN WIND SPEED CLOSE TO LOW
CENTRES IS LIKELY TO BE SHORT-LIVED
